Summary of Magma Results of Bristol Bay Sockeye Harvests 2018-2022

Tyler Dann

September 2023

This script will summarize magma results of 2018-2022 Bristol Bay district harvest.

Magma was run separately by Bobby for 2018, 2019 and 2022 and Tyler for 2020 and 2021 after the magmatization of ASL, genotypic, and harvest/strata definition data in this directory (V:\2_CentralBayof 2018-2022 District Harvest) and subdirectories for each year. Results were summarized in each years subdirectory and summary objects were saved. Magma summary objects include both stock composition and stock-specific age composition estimates summarized at three scales: individual stratum (e.g., Kvichak Section Set in 2021), district roll-ups (e.g., Naknek-Kvichak as a whole in 2021), and Bay-wide roll-ups for a year (e.g., Bristol Bay 2021). This documents the combining of those summaries, weighting of stock composition by harvests represented, and parsing out stock-specific harvests into stock- and age-specific harvests for each year at the Bay-wide level (Bristol Bay Harvest Brood Tables).

Note that because we have not been allocating a mixture to Igushik Section and WRSHA harvests in recent years those stock composition estimates are the average of all years we have estimates for in each area. I summarized the observed age composition in each area in each year to parse out stock-specific harvests into stock- and age-specific harvests for each area and add to the magma-sourced estimates. ASL samples were not collected from Igushik Section in 2020-2022 so I applied the overall Nushagak District age composition to harvests in those years (see below). These harvests are relatively small (Igushik averaged 473K, WRSHA 522K) so they should have a minimal impact on overall results.

Bring in harvests to weight stock and age comps

Here Im bringing in the harvests used by magma. These were the same harvests used to weight estimates in creating the model input files for Currys model. Then Im summing them up for annual harvests to weight the Bay-wide stocks comps with.

## Harvests were sent by Stacy and saved in this directory:
## V:\Analysis\2_Central\Sockeye\Bristol Bay\MAGMA of 2018-2022 District
## Harvest\Harvest from Stacy I formatted for magma into each years' data
## folder and will read in and summarize those

## 2018 harvests
Harvest_2018 <- read_table(file = "SBBAY18/data/harvestSBBAY18.txt")

## 2019 harvests
Harvest_2019 <- read_table(file = "SBBAY19/data/harvestSBBAY19.txt")

## 2020 harvests
Harvest_2020 <- read_table(file = "SBBAY20/data/harvestSBBAY20.txt")

## 2021 harvests
Harvest_2021 <- read_table(file = "SBBAY21/data/harvestSBBAY21.txt")

## 2022 harvests
Harvest_2022 <- read_table(file = "SBBAY22/2022/data/harvestSBBAY22.txt")

## Bundle harvests
AllHarvests <- bind_rows(Harvest_2018, Harvest_2019, Harvest_2020, Harvest_2021,
    Harvest_2022) %>%
    mutate(YEAR = factor(YEAR), SUBDISTRICT = factor(SUBDISTRICT), STAT_WEEK = factor(STAT_WEEK))

AnnualHarvests <- AllHarvests %>%
    group_by(YEAR) %>%
    summarize(AnnualHarvest = sum(HARVEST))

DT::datatable(AllHarvests) %>%
    formatRound(columns = 5, digits = 0)
DT::datatable(AnnualHarvests) %>%
    formatRound(columns = 2, digits = 0)

Weight each years overall Bay stock composition by harvest for total stock specific harvest and bundle harvests

OverallStockHarvests_2018 <- pop_2018_ho_bay$SBBAY %>%
    mutate(Harvest = AnnualHarvests %>%
        filter(YEAR == 2018) %>%
        select(AnnualHarvest) %>%
        pull()) %>%
    mutate(Harvest_Mean = Harvest * mean, Harvest_Median = Harvest * median, Harvest_Lower = Harvest *
        ci.05, Harvest_Upper = Harvest * ci.95) %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Mean, Harvest_Median, Harvest_Lower, Harvest_Upper) %>%
    mutate(Year = 2018)

OverallStockHarvests_2019 <- pop_2019_ho_bay$SBBAY %>%
    mutate(Harvest = AnnualHarvests %>%
        filter(YEAR == 2019) %>%
        select(AnnualHarvest) %>%
        pull()) %>%
    mutate(Harvest_Mean = Harvest * mean, Harvest_Median = Harvest * median, Harvest_Lower = Harvest *
        ci.05, Harvest_Upper = Harvest * ci.95) %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Mean, Harvest_Median, Harvest_Lower, Harvest_Upper) %>%
    mutate(Year = 2019)

OverallStockHarvests_2020 <- pop_2020_ho_bay$SBBAY %>%
    mutate(Harvest = AnnualHarvests %>%
        filter(YEAR == 2020) %>%
        select(AnnualHarvest) %>%
        pull()) %>%
    mutate(Harvest_Mean = Harvest * mean, Harvest_Median = Harvest * median, Harvest_Lower = Harvest *
        ci.05, Harvest_Upper = Harvest * ci.95) %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Mean, Harvest_Median, Harvest_Lower, Harvest_Upper) %>%
    mutate(Year = 2020)

OverallStockHarvests_2021 <- pop_2021_ho_bay$SBBAY %>%
    mutate(Harvest = AnnualHarvests %>%
        filter(YEAR == 2021) %>%
        select(AnnualHarvest) %>%
        pull()) %>%
    mutate(Harvest_Mean = Harvest * mean, Harvest_Median = Harvest * median, Harvest_Lower = Harvest *
        ci.05, Harvest_Upper = Harvest * ci.95) %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Mean, Harvest_Median, Harvest_Lower, Harvest_Upper) %>%
    mutate(Year = 2021)

OverallStockHarvests_2022 <- pop_2022_ho_bay %>%
    mutate(Harvest = AnnualHarvests %>%
        filter(YEAR == 2022) %>%
        select(AnnualHarvest) %>%
        pull()) %>%
    mutate(Harvest_Mean = Harvest * mean, Harvest_Median = Harvest * median, Harvest_Lower = Harvest *
        ci.05, Harvest_Upper = Harvest * ci.95) %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Mean, Harvest_Median, Harvest_Lower, Harvest_Upper) %>%
    mutate(Year = 2022)

AllOverallStockHarvests <- bind_rows(OverallStockHarvests_2018, OverallStockHarvests_2019,
    OverallStockHarvests_2020, OverallStockHarvests_2021, OverallStockHarvests_2022) %>%
    mutate(Year = factor(Year), group = factor(group, levels = c("Kuskokwim", "Togiak",
        "Igushik", "Wood", "Nushagak", "Kvichak", "Alagnak", "Naknek", "Egegik",
        "Ugashik", "North Peninsula")))

AllOverallStockHarvestsFig <- AllOverallStockHarvests %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = group, y = Harvest_Mean/1e+06, fill = Year)) + geom_col(position = "dodge") +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = Harvest_Lower/1e+06, ymax = Harvest_Upper/1e+06), width = 0.2,
        position = position_dodge(0.9)) + theme_bw() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90,
    hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5)) + scale_fill_viridis(discrete = TRUE, option = "H") +
    labs(title = "Stock-specific harvests in Bristol Bay 2018 - 2022", x = "Reporting Group",
        y = "Harvest (Millions) +/- 90% credible interval")

ggsave("AllOverallStockHarvestsFig.png", AllOverallStockHarvestsFig, device = "png",
    height = 6, width = 6, units = "in")

AllOverallStockHarvestsFig

    formatRound(columns = 2:5, digits = 0)

Bring in areas where averages were applied in terms of both stock- and age-specific harvests

Igushik Section and WRSHA harvests were parsed out to stock using historical stock comp averages when creating the district roll-ups for Currys model input files. Here Im summarizing harvests in those areas in 2018-2022 with harvest numbers from Stacy, bringing in those average stock comps, and observed age comps in each year from ASL data provided by Stacy. Note that no samples were collected from Igushik in 2020-2022 so age compositions are the overall Nushagak District age composition for each year.

Parse annual stock-specific harvests by stock-specific age composition - Igushik and WRSHA

## Bring in harvests
IgushikWRSHAHarvests <- read_csv("Harvest from Stacy/IgushikWRSHAHarvests.csv")

## Bring in age comps written out from other workspace
AllIgushikWRSHAAgeComps <- readRDS("ASL from Stacy/AllIgushikWRSHAAgeComps.RDs")

## Bring in historical averages we have been applying to harvests in recent
## years
EstDat2022 <- dget("V:/Analysis/2_Central/Sockeye/Bristol Bay/2022 District Harvest/Objects/EstDat2022.txt")

IgushikAverageStockComps <- EstDat2022 %>%
    filter(Mixture == "IgushikAverage") %>%
    select(group = Group, Mean)

## 2018 Igushik AllIgushikWRSHAAgeComps %>% filter(Year == 2018 & Area ==
## 'Igushik') %>% select(age) %>% unique()

IgushikHarvests_2018 <- OverallStockHarvests_2018 %>%
    select(group, Year) %>%
    mutate(Harvest = IgushikWRSHAHarvests %>%
        filter(Year == 2018) %>%
        select(Igushik) %>%
        pull()) %>%
    left_join(x = ., y = IgushikAverageStockComps) %>%
    mutate(StockHarvest = Harvest * Mean, `12` = StockHarvest * AllIgushikWRSHAAgeComps %>%
        filter(Year == 2018 & Area == "Igushik" & age == 12) %>%
        select(Prop) %>%
        pull(), `13` = StockHarvest * AllIgushikWRSHAAgeComps %>%
        filter(Year == 2018 & Area == "Igushik" & age == 13) %>%
        select(Prop) %>%
        pull())

## 2019 Igushik AllIgushikWRSHAAgeComps %>% filter(Year == 2019 & Area ==
## 'Igushik') %>% select(age) %>% unique()

IgushikHarvests_2019 <- OverallStockHarvests_2019 %>%

Parse annual stock-specific harvests by stock-specific age composition - 2018

Here Im bundling together the stock-specific age comps for each year and spreading out the Bay-wide stock-specific harvests summarized above out to age-specific harvests for each stock. Adding in Igushik/WRSHA stock- and age-specific estimates to magma estimated harvest brood table - left joining and summing columns the same name (overall stock-specific harvest and the six age classes that overlap).

AnnualAgeCompMeans_2018 <- bind_rows(stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(2)_DSBBAY_Togiak` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean), stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(3)_DSBBAY_Igushik` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean), stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(4)_DSBBAY_Wood` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean), stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(5)_DSBBAY_Nushagak` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean), stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(6)_DSBBAY_Kvichak` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean), stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(7)_DSBBAY_Alagnak` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean), stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(8)_DSBBAY_Naknek` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean), stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(9)_DSBBAY_Egegik` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean), stock_age_2018_ho_bay$`(10)_DSBBAY_Ugashik` %>%
    select(group, age, mean) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = age, values_from = mean))

HarvestBroodTable_2018 <- OverallStockHarvests_2018 %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Mean) %>%
    slice(2:10) %>%
    left_join(., y = AnnualAgeCompMeans_2018) %>%
    mutate(across(.cols = 3:14, ~.x * Harvest_Mean))

## Bundle up stock- and age-specific harvests from both Igushik and WRSHA to
## add to
BothIguWRSHAHarvestsCollapsed <- BothIguWRSHAHarvests %>%
    replace_na(replace = list(`12` = 0, `13` = 0, `14` = 0, `22` = 0, `23` = 0, `11` = 0)) %>%
    group_by(Year, group) %>%
    summarize(Harvest = sum(Harvest), StockHarvest = sum(StockHarvest), `12` = sum(`12`),
        `13` = sum(`13`), `14` = sum(`14`), `22` = sum(`22`), `23` = sum(`23`), `11` = sum(`11`))

## Add Igushik/WRSHA stock- and age-specific to magma estimated harvest brood
## table - left joining and summing columns the same name (overall
## stock-specific harvest and the six age classes that overlap)
HarvestBroodTable_2018_WithIgushikWRSHA <- left_join(HarvestBroodTable_2018, BothIguWRSHAHarvestsCollapsed %>%
    filter(Year == 2018), by = "group") %>%
    mutate(Harvest_Stock = Harvest_Mean + StockHarvest, `11` = `11.x` + `11.y`, `12` = `12.x` +
        `12.y`, `13` = `13.x` + `13.y`, `14` = `14.x` + `14.y`, `22` = `22.x` + `22.y`,
        `23` = `23.x` + `23.y`) %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Stock, `03`, `11`, `12`, `13`, `14`, `15`, `21`, `22`,
        `23`, `24`, `32`, `33`)

HarvestBroodTable_2018Fig <- HarvestBroodTable_2018_WithIgushikWRSHA %>%
    select(-Harvest_Stock) %>%
    pivot_longer(cols = 2:13, names_to = "Age", values_to = "Harvest") %>%
    mutate(group = factor(group, levels = c("Togiak", "Igushik", "Wood", "Nushagak",
        "Kvichak", "Alagnak", "Naknek", "Egegik", "Ugashik")), Age = factor(Age,
        levels = c("03", "11", "12", "13", "14", "15", "21", "22", "23", "24", "32",
            "33"))) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = group, y = Harvest, fill = Age)) + geom_col(position = "stack") +
    theme_bw() + scale_fill_viridis(discrete = TRUE, option = "H") + labs(title = "Stock- and age-specific harvests in Bristol Bay - 2018",
    x = "Stock")

write_csv(HarvestBroodTable_2018_WithIgushikWRSHA, file = "HarvestBroodTable_2018.csv")

DT::datatable(HarvestBroodTable_2018_WithIgushikWRSHA) %>%
    formatRound(2:14, digits = 0)
HarvestBroodTable_2018Fig

HarvestBroodTable_2022 <- OverallStockHarvests_2022 %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Mean) %>%
    slice(-c(4, 7)) %>%
    left_join(., y = AnnualAgeCompMeans_2022) %>%
    mutate(across(.cols = 3:11, ~.x * Harvest_Mean))

## Add Igushik/WRSHA stock- and age-specific to magma estimated harvest brood
## table - left joining and summing columns the same name (overall
## stock-specific harvest and the six age classes that overlap)
HarvestBroodTable_2022_WithIgushikWRSHA <- left_join(HarvestBroodTable_2022, BothIguWRSHAHarvestsCollapsed %>%
    filter(Year == 2022), by = "group") %>%
    mutate(Harvest_Stock = Harvest_Mean + StockHarvest, `12` = `12.x` + `12.y`, `13` = `13.x` +
        `13.y`, `14` = `14.x` + `14.y`, `22` = `22.x` + `22.y`, `23` = `23.x` + `23.y`) %>%
    select(group, Harvest_Stock, `12`, `13`, `14`, `22`, `23`, `24`, `32`, `33`)

HarvestBroodTable_2022Fig <- HarvestBroodTable_2022_WithIgushikWRSHA %>%
    select(-Harvest_Stock) %>%
    pivot_longer(cols = 2:9, names_to = "Age", values_to = "Harvest") %>%
    mutate(group = factor(group, levels = c("Togiak", "Igushik", "Wood", "Nushagak",
        "Kvichak", "Alagnak", "Naknek", "Egegik", "Ugashik")), Age = factor(Age,
        levels = c("12", "13", "14", "22", "23", "24", "32", "33"))) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = group, y = Harvest, fill = Age)) + geom_col(position = "stack") +
    theme_bw() + scale_fill_viridis(discrete = TRUE, option = "H") + labs(title = "Stock- and age-specific harvests in Bristol Bay - 2022",
    x = "Stock")

HarvestBroodTable_2022_WithIgushikWRSHA <- HarvestBroodTable_2022_WithIgushikWRSHA %>%
    mutate(group = factor(group, levels = c("Togiak", "Igushik", "Wood", "Nushagak",
        "Kvichak", "Alagnak", "Naknek", "Egegik", "Ugashik"))) %>%
    arrange(group)
